## The vault at a glance

Notes are markdown files with YAML frontmatter. The frontmatter `type` field is
how everything is routed â€” tools find files by `type`, not by guessing paths.

| Folder | What lives here | frontmatter `type` |
|--------|-----------------|--------------------|
| `Core/` | Identity: bio, values, goals, preferences, relationships, routines | `core` (one per `topic`), plus the generated `core-identity` |
| `Health/` | Health overview + metric logs (weight, sleep, mood, â€¦) | `health-overview`, `metric-log` |
| `Work/` | Work overview | `work-overview` |
| `Interests/` | One overview per interest, plus freeform notes | `interest-overview` |
| `Journal/` | Dated journal entries | `journal` |
| `Stream/` | Timestamped stream-of-consciousness (auto-created) | `stream` |
| `AI-Observations/` | Your scratchpad, patterns, nudges, weekly summaries | (managed by tools) |

## How to route a write

- **A number {{owner_name}} tracks over time** (weight, sleep hours, mood 1-10,
  a run): use `log_metric`. It finds the `type: metric-log` file whose
  `metric:` matches. If none exists, create one (see `recipes/01-add-a-tracker.md`).
- **A passing thought / brain-dump**: `log_stream`.
- **A new standalone note**: `create_note` with the right `type` in frontmatter.
- **Updating identity** (a fact about who {{owner_name}} is): `update_identity_field`
  (by `topic`) or edit the `Core/` note directly.
- **Something you noticed about {{owner_name}} mid-conversation**: `log_observation`
  (pick a `type` and a short `subject`). Don't announce it â€” just log it.
- **A recurring pattern** worth remembering: `log_pattern`.
- **Something {{owner_name}} said they want to do**: `log_nudge`, so you can hold
  them accountable later.

## How to read

- Start most sessions by calling `get_identity` to load who {{owner_name}} is.
- `search_vault` for semantic lookup; `find_notes` to fetch by frontmatter;
  `recent_journals` / `search_by_date` for time-based recall;
  `get_observations` to review your own past notes (patterns / nudges / scratchpad).

